{'post_title': '', 'post_text': "It's possible to make a site simpler and more straightforward for users by making it prettier. Really good web design is very subtle; things like giving small but definite visual cues for where posts begin and end, or making the &#34;reply&#34; link a slightly different color from the post so it doesn't look like part of the post -- these small changes do more than look pretty, they also lower the cognitive load on the user and make it feel simpler.\n\nA lot of what Reddit has been doing to their interface has been tiny changes that make it feel simpler. Good web design is something to be appreciated; great web design makes you forget that it's even there.", 'hanesst_id': 444, 'post_type': 'comment', 'post_parent': 388, 'username': 'sketerpot', 'pwd_hash': 'cT8KpNQ7mL', 'post_url': ''},
