{'post_title': '', 'post_text': 'While I agree that VC funding is not necessarily required to spark a startup, I do however believe that it can serve wonders in terms of building connections and publicity. Prominent bloggers, such as Michael Arrington and Peter Cashmore, hunt for news relating to startup fundings. Moreover, a VC firm brings high level connections from people with real experience in this game (Vinod Khosla, Ram Shriram, etc).<p>Almost all sufficiently large startups eventually require Venture Capitalists. So there is no hard and fast rule on this; just take the money when it makes sense.', 'hanesst_id': 799, 'post_type': 'comment', 'post_parent': 761, 'username': 'python_kiss', 'pwd_hash': 'MhJ5VBzoTs', 'post_url': ''},
