{'post_title': '', 'post_text': "If a seed firm has an official relationship with a VC, that VC will know which of their startups are best.  They can't invest in all of them, since the number of startups is so much larger at the seed phase. Any they don't invest in, other VCs will know are rejects.  And this is the kiss of death, because the most important thing to most VCs is other VCs' opinion. <p>Both Techstars and the new Lightspeed thing have this problem.  At Techstars one of the founders is a VC, and Lightspeed is itself a VC firm.", 'hanesst_id': 928, 'post_type': 'comment', 'post_parent': 926, 'username': 'pg', 'pwd_hash': 'Y89KIJ3frM', 'post_url': ''},
